results.wikipedia_summary: Attila is a genus of tropical passerine birds, the attilas. They belong to the tyrant flycatcher family. The species in this genus have large heads and hooked bills; they are markedly predatory and aggressive for their size â hence the scientific and common names, which refer to Attila the Hun.
